Step 1 - Click on services and type S3 in the search bar
Step 2 - Click create bucket
Step 3 - Type the details
Step 4 - Enable encryption and click create bucket
Step 5 - Type EC2 in the search bar
Step 6 - Click instance and click launch instance
Step 7 - Input details - Name and tag
Step 8 - Input network settings
Step 9 - Click advanced details, Create IAM details
Step 10 - Click create role
Step 11 - Click AWS Services
Step 12 - Choose EC2 and click next
Step 13 - Type S3fullaccess in the search bar and click
Step 14 - Choose SSMmanageinstancecore for the second role
Step 15 - Input role name and description - Click role
Step 16 - View the role created
Step 17 - Go back to the EC2 tab and choose S3andSSM role
Step 18 - Scroll down to user data, Copy and paste the EC2 bash script
Step 19 - Click create security group and choose HTTP, HTTPS, SSH (IP)
Step 20 - Choose a key pair you have
Step 21 - Click launch
Step 22 - Click view instances and copy & paste public IPV4 DNS in your browser
Step 23 - View the website
